      <!-- Ingredient cards -->
      <div class="ing-grid">
  
        <article class="ing-card ing-lift" tabindex="0">
          <div class="ing-eyebrow">Lift</div>
          <h3>Green-tea Caffeine</h3>
          <p>Steady focus from natural caffeine, without the sharp edge.</p>
          <ul class="ing-facts">
            <li><strong>Target per bar:</strong> ~<span class="mono">80 mg</span>*</li>
            <li><strong>Source:</strong> green tea extract</li>
            <li><strong>Reason:</strong> pairs well with L-theanine for calmer alertness</li>
          </ul>
          <details class="ing-evidence">
            <summary>Evidence snapshot</summary>
            <p>Moderate caffeine improves alertness and reaction time; when paired with L-theanine, studies report
               better task accuracy and fewer jitters (varies by dose and individual).<span class="note">‚Ä†</span></p>
          </details>
        </article>
  
        <article class="ing-card ing-smooth" tabindex="0">
          <div class="ing-eyebrow">Smooth</div>
          <h3>L-theanine</h3>
          <p>Promotes calm alertness and smooths caffeine‚Äôs lift.</p>
          <ul class="ing-facts">
            <li><strong>Typical range:</strong> <span class="mono">100‚Äì200 mg</span></li>
            <li><strong>Effect:</strong> supports attention with relaxed focus</li>
          </ul>
          <details class="ing-evidence">
            <summary>Evidence snapshot</summary>
            <p>Reviews note L-theanine increases alpha-wave activity (relaxed alertness). Combined with caffeine,
               it may reduce perceived stress and improve attention switching.</p>
          </details>
        </article>
  
        <article class="ing-card ing-hydrate" tabindex="0">
          <div class="ing-eyebrow">Hydrate</div>
          <h3>Electrolytes</h3>
          <p>Hydration supports cognition and endurance during long sessions.</p>
          <ul class="ing-facts">
            <li>Sodium ‚Ä¢ Potassium ‚Ä¢ Magnesium</li>
            <li>Helps maintain fluid balance for mental stamina</li>
          </ul>
          <details class="ing-evidence">
            <summary>Evidence snapshot</summary>
            <p>Even mild dehydration can impair mood and focus; electrolyte balance helps prevent those dips.</p>
          </details>
        </article>
  
        <article class="ing-card ing-adapt" tabindex="0">
          <div class="ing-eyebrow">Resilience</div>
          <h3>Adaptogens</h3>
          <p>Stress-support so focus actually sticks (e.g., rhodiola, ashwagandha).</p>
          <ul class="ing-facts">
            <li>Targets perceived fatigue and stress reactivity</li>
            <li>Complements caffeine‚Äôs alertness with composure</li>
          </ul>
          <details class="ing-evidence">
            <summary>Evidence snapshot</summary>
            <p>Emerging research suggests some adaptogens reduce fatigue and support stress adaptation in healthy
               adults; effects vary with dose and personal response.</p>
          </details>
        </article>
  
      </div>
  
      <!-- How it works -->
      <div class="hiw">
        <h3 class="hiw-title">How it works ‚Äî the quick version</h3>
        <ol class="hiw-steps">
          <li><span>1</span><strong>Lift</strong>: natural caffeine wakes up adenosine-fog ‚Äî no harsh spike.</li>
          <li><span>2</span><strong>Smooth</strong>: L-theanine modulates the lift ‚Üí calm focus, fewer jitters.</li>
          <li><span>3</span><strong>Hydrate</strong>: electrolytes keep the system balanced while you think.</li>
          <li><span>4</span><strong>Resilience</strong>: adaptogens help your brain stay in ‚Äúget-stuff-done‚Äù mode.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
  
      <!-- More Qs (fun + human) -->
      <div class="sc-faq">
        <details>
          <summary>Why green tea instead of coffee?</summary>
          <p>Green tea has a gentler curve and plays nicely with L-theanine. Coffee‚Äôs great ‚Äî we just wanted a
             carry-anywhere option with fewer spikes and no brewing.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>When should I use Buzzbar?</summary>
          <p>Morning classes, deep-work blocks, pre-meeting boosts, travel days. If caffeine-sensitive, start with half.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Medical advice?</summary>
          <p>No ‚Äî this is food, not medicine. If pregnant, nursing, or managing a condition, talk to your clinician
             before using caffeine or adaptogens.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
  
      <p class="sc-foot">
        *Targets shown during pre-release and may change as we finalize the formula.
        <span class="note">‚Ä† Evidence snapshots are summary notes of published research; individual responses vary.</span>
      </p>
  
    </div>
